About the job
\U0001f5c2 We’re Hiring: Entry-Level Software Developer
 \U0001f552 Employment Type: Full-Time
 \U0001f4bc Level: Entry-Level
We are looking for a passionate and motivated Entry-Level Software Developer to join our development team. In this role, you will work alongside experienced engineers to design, develop, and maintain software applications. This is a great opportunity to build your skills, gain hands-on experience, and grow your career in software development.
If you are eager to learn, enjoy coding, and love solving problems, we’d love to hear from you!
\U0001f3af Key Responsibilities
Assist in developing, testing, and maintaining software applications
Write clean, efficient, and well-documented code
Collaborate with team members to design and implement new features
Debug and troubleshoot software issues
Participate in code reviews and team meetings
Learn and apply best practices in software development
Support system integration and deployment activities
Document technical processes and workflows
\u2705 Requirements
Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or related field (or equivalent practical experience)
Basic knowledge of programming languages (e.g., Java, Python, JavaScript, C#)
Understanding of software development concepts and lifecycle (SDLC)
Familiarity with databases (SQL or NoSQL) is a plus
Knowledge of version control systems (e.g., Git)
Strong problem-solving and analytical skills
Willingness to learn and adapt to new technologies
Good communication and teamwork skills
Internship, academic projects, or coding portfolio is an advantage
\U0001f31f What We Offer
Mentorship and guidance from experienced developers
Opportunities for career growth and skill development
Exposure to real-world projects and modern technologies
Collaborative and innovative work environment
Competitive salary and benefits package
Training and learning resources

