About the job
Job Title: Systems Engineer

Project: LAND4140

Location: Canberra or Melbourne

Clearance: NV1 (Mandatory)

About The Role

This role sits within CASG supporting the LAND4140 program. The Systems Engineer will be responsible for coordinating and delivering systems engineering activities across the project lifecycle.

You will work closely with both engineering and commercial teams to ensure alignment between technical artefacts and broader program and commercial objectives.

Key Responsibilities 

 Coordinate and deliver assigned systems engineering activities 
 Conduct tender evaluations as part of a Tender Evaluation Working Group 
 Develop and refine system requirements 
 Provide technical systems engineering input, including drafting and reviewing:
 Statements of Work (SOW) 
 CDRLs, DIDs, and DSDs 
 Review and assess contract deliverables 
 Support development of key engineering plans, including:
 Systems Engineering Management Plan (SEMP) 
 Test & Evaluation Master Plan (TEMP) 
 Safety Management Plan 
 Configuration Management Plan 
 Support documentation for Government submissions 
 Provide engineering advice to support Landworthiness compliance 
 Lead or contribute to engineering tasks and teams 

Core Experience Required 

 Strong experience within CASG and Defence acquisition environments 
 Deep understanding of the One Defence Capability System (ODCS) lifecycle 
 Experience across Defence capital acquisition projects 
 Ability to perform complex engineering analysis and evaluation 
 Experience ensuring materiel compliance with legislative, policy, and regulatory frameworks 
 Exposure to:
 Engineering change processes (including Configuration Control Boards) 
 Technical certification and compliance 
 Defence engineering policies, processes, and plans 
 Ability to develop and review systems engineering artefacts across the full lifecycle 
 Familiarity with:
 CASG Engineering Management System (EMS) 
 CMTL and ERP frameworks 
 Strong stakeholder engagement and communication skills 
 Ability to work independently under limited direction 

Desired Experience

 Experience within the Land domain 
 Experience leading engineering teams or workstreams 


Qualifications & Requirements

 Bachelor's degree in Engineering (or equivalent) 
 Minimum 7+ years' recent Defence industry experience 
 Demonstrated Systems Engineering experience 
 Strong understanding of Defence systems engineering frameworks 
 NV1 Security Clearance (active) 
 Chartered Engineer status (preferred)

