About the job
Lead Software Engineer
Location: Remote

About Aeva
Aeva AI is the standard for AI phone answering in allied health. We answer every patient call with the most lifelike voice on the market — booking appointments, handling reschedules, and managing inquiries 24/7.
$0 to $1M+ ARR in under 14 months. 350+ practices across Australia, UK, and New Zealand. Bootstrapped, profitable, scaling fast.
Stack: Node.js, Express, TypeScript, React, PostgreSQL, with integrations into Cliniko, Stripe, Twilio, and VAPI for voice AI.

The Role
This is a full-time remote role for a Lead Software Engineer. You'll own the technical direction of our platform — setting up robust engineering processes, improving code quality, and accelerating our integration roadmap. You'll work above our existing developers, establishing the systems and standards that let the team ship faster with fewer bugs.
Our immediate priority is expanding our practice management system integrations. The foundations are in place; you'll refine the architecture, establish the patterns, and make future integrations faster to roll out. Beyond integrations, you'll shape everything from infrastructure to product features.
This is hands-on. You'll write code, not just manage.

What You'll Do
Own technical direction across the platform
Accelerate our PMS integration roadmap — refining existing architecture and shipping new integrations
Set up engineering processes and standards that make the team faster and more reliable
Mentor, unblock, and level up the dev team through code review and collaboration
Hands-on development — you'll still write and review code
Drive technical decisions and own delivery quality

Who Thrives Here
Operated at multiple levels — you've seen how engineering works at scale, but you're not precious about process when speed matters
Ship-first mentality — you know when good enough is good enough
Take ownership — you fix problems, not assign blame
Communicate clearly — you can explain technical decisions without overcomplicating things
Use AI tools fluently — Claude, Cursor, Copilot are part of your daily workflow

Requirements
8+ years software development experience
Strong backend: Node.js, TypeScript, PostgreSQL
Experience setting up engineering processes at growing companies
Worked at both startups and larger/enterprise companies
Can architect systems AND implement them
Comfortable with ambiguity and moving fast

Nice to Have
Healthcare software or SaaS experience
Voice AI integration experience
Experience with Make.com, Zapier, or n8n

Why Aeva
Real impact — your work ships to production and affects real clinics within days, not quarters
Growth trajectory — clear path to CTO as we scale the team
Profitable — bootstrapped, not burning runway
Hard problems — multi-system integration, voice AI, healthcare data. Not CRUD apps.
Small team, high trust — no bureaucracy, direct access to founders, autonomy to do your best work

Compensation
Discussions from $120,000 AUD, with room to grow based on impact.

