About the job
Our client is currently seeking experienced Python Developer to support a federal government program delivering a complex data management system used across international partners. This role will focus on the ongoing development, enhancement, and support of a web-based platform managing meteorological and ocean data.

You will work within a collaborative team environment, contributing to system development, cloud deployment, technical documentation, and stakeholder engagement across both local and international users.

Accountabilities and Responsibilities:
Design, develop, and maintain a web-based data management system across the full stack
Manage the end-to-end software development lifecycle, including design, build, testing, deployment, and support
Work with technologies including Python, PostgreSQL, JavaScript, and PHP
Support deployment and maintenance across on-premise and AWS cloud environments
Develop and maintain technical documentation and training materials
Deliver training and provide support to technical and non-technical users
Collaborate with internal teams and international stakeholders to enhance system capabilities
Support data ingestion, validation, and quality assurance processes

 Skills and experience we are looking for:
Strong experience as a Full-Stack Developer within web-based application environments
Proficiency in Linux (Ubuntu), PostgreSQL, Python, HTML/PHP, and JavaScript
Experience working with cloud platforms, particularly AWS
Experience across the full software development lifecycle in complex environments
Strong problem-solving skills and ability to work autonomously
Excellent communication skills with the ability to engage with a broad range of stakeholders
Must be an Australian Citizen to be considered.

 Highly regarded:
Experience working with data-intensive systems or scientific/environmental datasets
Experience developing training materials and delivering technical training
Exposure to government or international program environments
Willingness and ability to undertake short-term international travel
If you would like to know more, please contact Milly Kerei-Keepa on 0476865411/milly.kerei-keepa@talentinternational.com or hit Apply Now

