About the job
Windows Server, Office 365, Networking, Active Directory

Information Technology Engineer

A company who works in delivering cutting-edge solutions in cloud computing, cybersecurity, and comprehensive support services tailored specifically for public sector clients.

$85,000 + Super
To apply click on the link or email your CV to Jack.ford@searchability.com.au or call me on
0480 525 754 for more information.
Windows, Office 365, Active Directory, Azure, Networking
Candidates must have full right to work in Australia.

WHO ARE WE?...

A Managed Service who specializes in delivering comprehensive cloud solutions, cybersecurity expertise, and dedicated support tailored for public sector clients. With a focus on 24/7 support, proactive monitoring, and compliance management, they ensure seamless operations while safeguarding sensitive data. Their customized approach, coupled with a commitment to excellence, empowers public sector organizations to leverage technology effectively, mitigate risks, and achieve their strategic goals with confidence.

WHAT WILL YOU BE DOING?

As an L2 Engineer within the team, you’ll be the second escalation point of contact for IT support, handling a wide range of technical issues across cloud platforms, cybersecurity, and user support. Your day will involve diagnosing and troubleshooting hardware, software, and network issues while providing responsive assistance to end users. You’ll work closely with senior engineers to escalate complex problems and ensure smooth IT operations for our public sector clients. Additionally, you'll perform basic system administration tasks like password resets, user account management, and software updates. Clear communication will be key, as you'll document solutions, maintain our knowledge base, and keep users informed throughout the resolution process.

YOU NEED TO HAVE...

A proactive approach to learning new technologies and adapting to change
Hands-on experience with M365 tools (Teams, SharePoint Online, Exchange Online)
Strong troubleshooting skills for software, hardware, and basic networking (DNS, DHCP, VPNs)
The ability to provide friendly and efficient customer support
Good time management skills to juggle multiple support tickets effectively


TO BE CONSIDERED…

Please either apply by clicking online or emailing me directly to Jack.Ford@searchability.com.au For further information please call me on 0430 525 754. I can make myself available outside of normal working hours to suit from 7am until 10pm. If unavailable, please leave me a message. By applying for this role, you give express consent for us to process and submit (subject to required skills) your application to our client in conjunction with this vacancy only. Also feel free to connect with me on LinkedIn! I look forward to hearing from you.

Key Skills
Windows Server, Office 365, Networking, Active Directory

