About the job
At UTS, we’re changing the game. We’re on a journey to be the leading university of technology and we’re moving the world forward with our breakthroughs. We work at the nexus of creativity, technology and innovation and we want bright minds and constantly curious people to help us make it happen. As a young university, our goal is to connect, collaborate and make an impact with purpose and passion.

About the role

Are you an experienced Integration Developer looking to make an impact in a dynamic, cloud-driven environment? We’re seeking a skilled professional to troubleshoot, understand, and enhance integration workflows, APIs, and connectors that ensure seamless data exchange across applications on AWS, Boomi, and Denodo, all within the time-sensitive demands of critical business issues.

In this role, you’ll leverage your experience with integration technologies—from APIs and message brokers to data transformation frameworks—while delivering seamless, nondisruptive operations to daily business data flows. Prior experience with Boomi is essential, and familiarity with AWS, Denodo and Kafka is a plus. This role is also based in Sydney and requires the candidate to be onsite two days a week, therefore only candidates in the Sydney region will be considered.

If you have a passion for problem-solving and delivering top-tier IT support in a fast-paced environment, we want to hear from you!

If you have a deep understanding of integration best practices, security protocols, and API authentication, and are eager to contribute to innovative solutions, we’d love to hear from you!

About you

You are an experienced engineer, proficient in integration tools and middleware, including Boomi AtomSphere, APIs, and microservices. With strong communication skills, you effectively convey technical concepts and collaborate with stakeholders. You have a strong sense of urgency and proactively maintain assigned production support tickets, ensuring timely updates sent to impacted users while progressing bug fixes. You maintain meticulous design, development, and testing standards, prioritize security and data privacy, and are committed to staying updated with evolving integration technologies. You are also experienced in agile methodologies, contributing to successful team collaborations and high-quality outcomes. Other requirements include:

A relevant tertiary qualification or equivalent experience, with experience in developing and implementing integration solutions across diverse technology landscapes using DevSecOps practices
Has an awareness of ITIL processes and effectively use them as guide in daily operations
Identifying opportunities to enhance integration efficiency, optimise data exchange
Diagnose and troubleshoot technical issues that may arise in current live integrations
Support the design, development, and implementation of integrations
Ability to understand an integration process and translate it into its corresponding business impacts to aid prioritisation of work

For the full list of role responsibilities and selection criteria please download the position description from the documents section below!

Remuneration and Benefits 

Base Salary Range: $107,402 - $118,813 p.a. (HEW 7) depending on experience plus 17% superannuation (pension) in addition to the base salary.

The position is full-time and will be made on a continuing basis.

We offer a comprehensive range of benefits designed to support professional growth, personal well-being, and work-life balance. With programs like Fitness Passport and on-campus health services, we prioritise physical and mental wellness. Employees enjoy access to leadership programs, promotional opportunities, alongside study time support. We also offer flexible working arrangements, generous leave entitlements, childcare support, and research grants, ensuring a balanced and enriching work environment.

How to Apply 

Please click 'apply’ and include the following in your application:

A cover letter stating your motivation for applying for this
A copy of your resume

Only those applications submitted via the UTS online recruitment system will be accepted.

Please ensure that the file name for each document submitted includes the reference number IRC333562 and your name.

General enquiries or issues with your application may be directed to the UTS Recruitment Team at recruitment@uts.edu.au.

Closing Date: Wednesday 15 April 2026 at 11.59pm (AEST)

You must have unrestricted work rights in Australia for the duration of this employment to apply. Visa sponsorship is not available for this appointment. 

UTS prioritises safety, respect, and inclusion for every member of our community. In support of this, and in line with our statutory obligations under the National Code to Prevent and Respond to Gender-Based Violence 2026, all prospective employees must declare any past investigations relating to gender-based violence. Employment at UTS is contingent upon completion of this declaration, and, where necessary, assessment of any identified risk factors. We appreciate your role in upholding the standards and behaviour expected of our community.

