About the job
Design, build and improve web applications that matter.

Join ACER’s Software Development team as a Front\u2011End Developer on a 6\u2011month fixed\u2011term, full\u2011time contract, collaborating on digital solutions that support education and research on a global scale.

This role is aligned to a time\u2011sensitive project for a prominent Australian client, offering an exciting opportunity to contribute to innovative, high\u2011impact interactive assessment solutions.

ABOUT ACER
The Australian Council for Educational Research (ACER) is an international, independent, not\u2011for\u2011profit organisation committed to improving learning through world\u2011class research, assessments and digital innovation. With around 400 staff across Australia, India, Malaysia, the UAE and the UK, ACER delivers impactful educational solutions worldwide.
Our Software Development team, within the Information Technology Division, works collaboratively across ACER to design, build and maintain high\u2011quality digital products that enable meaningful research and assessment programs.

ABOUT THE ROLE
We are looking for a mid\u2011level Front\u2011End Developer with strong JavaScript skills to support a critical project delivering interactive assessments.

In this role, you will:
Build interactive assessment modules based on established designs
Contribute to solution design, development and quality assurance
Take ownership of code quality, accessibility, security and maintainability
Troubleshoot and resolve issues as they arise

You’ll work closely with the Lead Software Engineer, Assessment Developers, UX Designers and Software Testers as part of a supportive, collaborative team.

WHAT YOU'LL BRING

Essential experience and skills:
3+ years’ commercial experience in JavaScript front\u2011end/web development
Strong object\u2011oriented design and development skills
Experience developing high\u2011quality, interactive web interfaces
Experience with PHP and/or Java in a commercial environment
Solid database design and SQL knowledge
Understanding of modern software development lifecycles and practices
Ability to deliver to project timelines in a self\u2011managed way
Clear communication skills and strong attention to detail

Qualifications:
Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science (or equivalent experience)

ABOUT YOU
You’re a capable and adaptable developer who enjoys working in a fixed\u2011term, project\u2011based role. You take pride in quality work, communicate clearly, and value collaboration within a technical team.

WHY JOIN ACER?
Purpose\u2011driven organisation with global impact
Inclusive, collaborative and values\u2011led culture
Opportunity to contribute to meaningful digital initiatives over a defined period

HOW TO APPLY
Be part of software development that supports better learning outcomes worldwide.
\U0001f449 Apply via LinkedIn or view the full position description at:
https://www.acer.org/au/about-us/careers

Applications close: Thursday, 16 April 2026 at midnight (AEST)

ACER is an equal opportunity employer committed to diversity, inclusion and accessibility. Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander people are encouraged to apply. Adjustments can be requested at any stage of the recruitment process by contacting p&c@acer.org.

