About the job
Senior Software Engineer

\U0001f4cd Tingalpa, QLD | Hybrid | 4.5\u2011Day Work Week

Build world\u2011leading software for mission\u2011critical solutions.

Grabba Technologies Group is an Australian leader in biometric and identity technology—and the only mobile biometric hardware manufacturer in Australia. Based in Tingalpa, Queensland, we bring together nearly 100 years of complex manufacturing and technology expertise to support a global network of customers who rely on secure, efficient mobile identity solutions.

As we continue to grow, we’re looking for a Senior Software Engineer to play a key role in delivering innovative, reliable software that outpaces the market and sets new industry standards.

About the Role

As a Senior Software Engineer at Grabba, you’ll be a senior member of our software development team, working at the intersection of architecture, delivery, and operations.

Reporting to the Engineering Manager, you’ll take a hands\u2011on leadership role—shaping technical direction, mitigating risk across the full software lifecycle, and ensuring our solutions perform flawlessly in production. You’ll collaborate closely with engineers, stakeholders, and customers to turn complex requirements into robust, real\u2011world outcomes.

What You’ll Be Responsible For

Act as a senior contributor within the software engineering team, promoting technical excellence, collaboration, and continuous improvement
Lead software architecture, design, and implementation decisions
Proactively identify and mitigate technical risks across the development lifecycle
Oversee operational aspects of software delivery, including CI/CD pipelines, deployments, monitoring, reliability, and uptime
Take accountability for production performance, incident resolution, and post\u2011incident improvements
Mentor and support team members, fostering best practices and professional growth
Lead code reviews, technical approvals, and design discussions to ensure quality and consistency
Work closely with internal stakeholders and customers to deliver a high\u2011quality, reliable solution

About You

You’re an experienced, pragmatic senior developer who thrives in environments where reliability, performance, and accountability matter.

You’ll bring:

A Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field
5+ years’ experience in a senior (or equivalent) software development role
5–7+ years of hands\u2011on software development experience across one or more programming languages
Strong experience with modern software operations: CI/CD automation, deployment reliability, monitoring, and production system management
A solid understanding of product development from concept through long\u2011term production support
Exposure to ML/AI technologies (desirable but not essential)
Strong analytical skills and a practical, solution\u2011focused mindset
A demonstrated track record of delivering reliable, high\u2011impact software in collaborative teams

Our Values

At Grabba, values matter. We’re looking for someone who aligns with the way we think and operate:

Innately Positive – Passionate, positive, and caring
Obsessive About Progress – Always moving forward
Outpace and Outperform – Swifter, smarter, sharper
Disrupt Everything – The status quo is our enemy
Solutions\u2011Centred – Focused on what’s possible

Why Join Grabba?

We believe our people are our greatest asset, and we work hard to create an environment where they can thrive:

Hybrid working – a balanced mix of home and office
4.5\u2011day work week – finish at 12:00 pm every Friday
Paid birthday leave – enjoy your birthday your way
Career growth in a dynamic, global business
Ongoing learning and development opportunities

If you’re ready to build high\u2011impact software in a company that values progress, accountability, and innovation, we’d love to hear from you.

